social_posts.post_text: Picture? I hardly know her! 📸 I 🫶 my photopass fam so muchh

2022, what a year. Reflecting on this year I realized it may have been one of the most rewarding years of my life. I graduated college, traveled to Scotland, got to celebrate one of my childhood best friends getting married and another get engaged. I finally received my lupus diagnosis after years of searching for answers. I began working at Disney World with some of the most amazing, talented, and kind people I’ve ever met. I pushed myself out of my comfort zone time and time again this year and by doing so I’ve learned so much about myself. I’m giving myself a great big hug this New Years, and I think you should too 💌 sending you all well wishes and love for 2023. Happy New Year! #2022 #newyear
26 ♥️ thank you for all the well wishes and to everyone who made my birthday so incredibly special, you make my heart full. I’m the luckiest girl in the universe 🥹

This January I completed my Disney College Program as a Photopass Photographer at Epcot. Without a doubt the thing I’m most grateful about from this experience are the friends I made. Never before have I met a group of people so kind and so eager to help others. Thanks for the mems Epcot fam :) 🫶

March ❤️ March was a month of celebration. I celebrated two of my dear friends getting married, I celebrated my Papaw’s 89th birthday, and I celebrated my Lupus medication finally getting approved by my insurance after weeks of anxiously waiting. I am so thankful for my friends and family, for warmer weather, for book clubs, for the lizards that sunbathe on my windowsill and for my cat that watches them.
happy birthday @keving43 <3

One minute we’re squeezed onto the same office chair taking turns playing Oregon Trail on the family computer and the next we’re celebrating your 30th birthday. Meg, no matter how many birthdays pass you’ll always be my infinitely cooler big sister 🤎🌈✨
